data.description:
We want to create a testing utility called 'ito' that can take a message and a callback, returning true if every use of expecto returns true in the callback.

An example of usage:
```
ito("feels good after eats a pickle", ()=> {
  var forestWeasel = new Weasel();
  var pickle = new Pickle();
  forestWeasel.eat(pickle);
  expecto(forestWeasel.feeling).toBe("good"); 
})
```
Note we use the names expecto instead of expect, and ito instead of it, so as not to overwrite the kata testing framework's it and expect.

Requirements:
- expecto and ito should be functions in the global namespace.
- expecto.toBe should compare using strict equality ===
